div1.p:
UNITED STATES OF AMERICA.
Territory of Washington, County of King ss.
To the Sheriff or any Constable and the keeper of the jail of said King County WHEREAS, at a Justice's Court held at my office, in said county, for the Examination trial of of William Jewett for the offense hereinafter stated, the said William Jewett being charged with the crime of seduction, and said examination having been was convicted of having, on the day of 18 , in said county committed continued until 8th day of April 1889 and it having been and upon conviction, the said Court did adjudge and determined that said by the Court that there is probable cause to change William Jewett defendant herein with the crime of seduction and that said dollars, and dollars costs and stand committed until the William Jewett be held to await the action of the preliminary examination same be paid: and, whereas, the said has made to be held before me with bail fixed in the sum of $1000 and whereas the default in the payment of the same. Therefore, you, the said Constable said William Jewett has made default in said bail in said amount are hereby commanded in the name of the United States forthwith to convery and deliver the said William Jewett to the said keeper; and you, the said keeper, are hereby commanded to receive the said William Jewett into your custody in said jail and him there keep until cleared by due proccess of law or unless bail be sooner furnished at hard labor for the space of fine and costs be sooner paid, or he shall thence be discharged by due course of law. Dated this 5th day of April 1889 John F. Miller Justice of the Peace. SEAL. Seattle Precinct King County Washington Territory
